    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="810"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.2222/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Greek
                        Ambassador (<persName type="to">Diamantopoulos</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-12">December 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to refer to my note of
                    October 30, 1942,<note n="95" xml:id="d810fn95">Not printed.</note> regarding
                    the formation of separate battalions of Greek subjects in the Army of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>There is quoted below the text of a communication on this subject which has been
                    received from the War Department: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The War Department is initiating action to form an Infantry Battalion
                            with Greek Nationals at an early date. Announcement of <pb facs="0828"
                                n="822" xml:id="pg_822"/> this action will be made to the public at
                            the Secretary of War’s next press conference.”<note n="96"
                                xml:id="d810fn96">Announcement was made by the War Department on
                                December 12, 1942.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
